$
$        THE FOLLOWING CODES ARE USED TO INCLUDE AND EXCLUDE
$        BLOCKS OF SOURCE
$  
$        C** = STUFF FOR THIS VERSION ONLY.
$        CN* = STUFF FOR ALL VERSIONS EXCEPT THIS ONE.
$  
$        WHERE **, * ARE LETTERS IDENTIFYING THE VERSION:
$  
$    the old (not recently compiled & checked) versions:
$        IB, I = IBM mainframes
$        DC, D = CDC
$        RA, R = CRAY
$        VA, V = non-alpha VAX/vms
$
$    The modern IBM/RS6000 and DEC-alpha/VMS version do not have
$    and specific machine prefix.  Both use the CI3E prefix
$  
$    THE FOLLOWING ARE GENERIC PREFIXES
$
$       COM - Fixed-size allocator in a common block version
$       CGRAB - dynamic-sized allocator 
$          one of these two options must be choosen in the
$          machine-specific GRAB subroutine (RS6000STUFF, ALPHASTUFF)
$
$       CNOLOC - provides a dummy  LOC() .  This should be avoided
$          because clebsch will give wrong results if the log(factorial)
$          table has to be used.
$
$       CI3E - ieee arithmatic - the Dec Alpha version is made
$               using this and  /float=ieee
$  
$       CSP - MACHINES WITH SPEAKEASY KEEP/GET (IBM, VAX)
$       CAP - MACHINES WITHOUT SPEAKEASY KEEP/GET (CDC CRAY)
$  
$     coupled channels:
$       C4F - C.C. F & G ARRAY IS TO BE REAL*4 (NORMAL)
$       C8F - C.C. F & G ARRAY IS TO BE REAL*8
$  
$     coupled channels:
$       C4H - C.C. HOMO & SOLN. ARRAY IS TO BE REAL*4  This
$            might be broken by now
$       C8H - C.C. HOMO & SOLN. ARRAY IS TO BE REAL*8 (NORMAL)
$  
$        THE FIRST LINE LISTS PREFIXES TO BE STRIPPED OFF OF THE SOURCE
$        LINE, THUS ACTIVATING THE LINE OR EXPOSING THE NEXT PREFIX.
$        THE SECOND LINE LISTS PREFIXES WHICH WILL CAUSE MORTRAN TO
$        DELETE THE ENTIRE LINE.
$           EXAMPLES:  THE FIRST 2 LINES FOR THE VARIOUS old VERSIONS ARE:
$  
$  
$  CIB COS CND CDX CNR CNV CIE CHR CWX CSP CDO CFR C4F C4H   IBM (OS)
$  CDE CVE
$  
$  CDC CDE CNI CNR CNV CWD CAP CDM ...      CDC VERSION
$  CDX CVE CIE CWX
$  
$  CRA CNI CNV CDX CND CWD CAP CDO CVX CIX C8F C8H       CRAY VERSION
$  CRX CVE CIE CDE CWX
$  
$  CVA CVE CNI CND CDX CNR CHR CWX CSP CDM      old DEC VAX/VMS
$  CDE
